node.title: Man dies after homemade bomb explodes in car
node.description: The man was wearing a homemade explosive vest.
node.content: ["A Melbourne man has died after a homemade bomb exploded in his car while he was driving on Saturday.", "The man was wearing an explosive vest which was triggered after he drove over a speed bump on Young Rd in the suburb of Hallam.", "The car continued travelling a few hundred metres after the explosion before hitting a parked car, according to 7News.\u00a0", "Emergency services were called to the scene just before lunchtime. The suburb was immediately put into lockdown while police investigated.\u00a0", "A local resident told 7News the police spent an entire day removing the device and debris before reopening the street.\u00a0\u00a0", "\"They had the streets blocked off and police pretty much controlling everything, there was 15 police cars all around the place,\" they told the outlet.\u00a0", "\"I just heard a big loud band at about 11am and I looked out the window and saw the car had gone through the roundabout and crashed into a sign,\" another local said.\u00a0", "The man is understood to be a 43-year-old former soldier from Dandenong, 7News reports.\u00a0", "Police said the explosion could have been much worse given the proximity to homes and an aged care facility.\u00a0", "Arson and explosive squad officers are investigating the man's death but it's not being treated as suspicious.\u00a0\u00a0"]
